II. Licensing
The UNFCCC secretariat licenses high-resolution, high quality and archival audio and video recordings (“Audiovisual Materials”) of the plenary sessions of the Conference of the Parties to the Convention, the Conference of the Parties serving as the meeting of the Parties to the Kyoto Protocol and the Conference of the Parties serving as the meeting of the Parties to the Paris Agreement, as well as the plenary sessions of their subsidiary bodies.
All UNFCCC audiovisual materials are not in the public domain: they are the property of the UNFCCC secretariat and their copyright is owned by the UNFCCC secretariat.
For more information on licensing requirements and how to submit a request, please contact the Communications and Engagement Division,
webmaster@unfccc.int
